The `Collection.Option` is an aliased map and you should be able to do something like: `Options: types.JsonMap{"query": "YOUR QUERY"},`.
Alternatively, you can also use the typed `models.CollectionViewOptions` struct and load it via `models.Collection.SetOptions(options)` method:
```
collection := &models.Collection{ ...
}
collection.SetOptions(models.CollectionViewOptions{
Query: "YOUR QUERY",
})
```
In both cases note that you don't have to specify the `Schema` field because for the "View" collections it will be autogenerated from the query (*there are plans in the future to allow custom user defined schema for the views*).

